					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13758856#post-4782337</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13758856/scp-5078#post-4782337</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sat, 26 Sep 2020 01:55:07 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Vezaz</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1403034</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>There were more Russian translators in America than ever during the Cold War. And even if there is an in-universe justification, it just doesn't work for me. I'd rather read your characters' dialogue and their story, rather than try to decode it.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13758856#post-4782331</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13758856/scp-5078#post-4782331</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sat, 26 Sep 2020 01:31:06 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Amelia Wright</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>3754950</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Heya, thanks for getting to me. The spelling is intentional. First off the piece is set in the Coldest War. Anti-Russian sentiment is rising, and the Foundation has limited access to Russian translators.</p> <p>Also, in the piece, the Russian translator was unable to properly translate the alternate reality Russian. It's a different type then ours, and they're understanding of both English and our Russian is skewed.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13758856#post-4782306</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13758856/scp-5078#post-4782306</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sat, 26 Sep 2020 00:22:27 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Vezaz</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1403034</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I could get behind this article except for the Russians speaking in broken english. They don't have phones or radios in Indiana? They don't have white guys who speak Russian? :P It's a very awkward choice, and the resulting dialogue takes me out of the story because it sounds silly.</p> <p>If you rewrote this so the Russians could just talk like normal human beings through an interpreter, I could see what you were going for much better. For now, got to downvote.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
